{"parse":{"title":"teacher","pageid":48383,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{swp}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|techere}}, equivalent to {{suf|en|teach|er|id2=agent noun}}. More at {{m|en|teach}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{a|en|non-rhotic}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈtiː.t͡ʃəː/|[ˈtʰɪi̯.t͡ʃəː]|a=RP}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-uk-teacher.ogg|a=UK}}\n*** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-teacher.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{a|en|rhotic}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈti.t͡ʃɚ/|[ˈtʰɪi̯.t͡ʃɚ]|~|[ˈtʰɪi̯.t͡ʃɹ̩]|a=GA,[[w:Standard Canadian English|Standard Canadian]]}}\n*** {{audio|en|en-us-teacher.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{rhymes|en|iːtʃə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n* {{hyph|en|tea|cher}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A person who [[teach]]es, especially one employed in a [[school]]; preceptor.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-07-19|author=[http://www.theguardian.com/profile/marktran Mark Tran]\n|volume=189|issue=6|page=1|magazine=w:The Guardian Weekly\n|title=[http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2013/jul/12/war-denying-children-education Denied an education by war]\n|passage=One particularly damaging, but often ignored, effect of conflict on education is the proliferation of attacks on schools{{...}}as children, '''teachers''' or school buildings become the targets of attacks. Parents fear sending their children to school. Girls are particularly vulnerable to sexual violence.}}\n# The [[index finger]]; the [[forefinger]].\n# An [[indication]]; a [[lesson]].\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=w:Steve LeVine|title= Trump Speech to Congress: The Message Was Trumpian, But The Tone Was Decidedly Not|work=w:Quartz|url=https://qz.com/921758/trump-speech-to-congress-the-message-was-trumpian-but-the-tone-was-decidedly-not/|date=28 February 2017|passage=But if the last two years are a '''teacher''', look for the bombastic tweets to resume before sunrise.}}\n# {{lb|en|Mormonism}} The second highest office in the [[w:Aaronic priesthood|Aaronic priesthood]], held by priesthood holders of at least the age of 14.\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|person who teaches}} {{l|en|preceptor}}, {{l|en|educator}}\n* {{sense|index finger}} See [[Thesaurus:index finger]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en|co-teacher|parent-teacher organization|failure is the best teacher\n|e-teacher|pupil teacher\n|experience is the best teacher\n|head teacher\n|home teacher| pastor-teacher\n|parent-teacher association\n|relief teacher|coteacher|cyberteacher|ex-teacher|exteacher|headteacher|microteacher|nonteacher|subteacher|superteacher|teacherage|teachercentric|teacherdom|teachered|teacherese|teacherhood|teachering|teacherish|teacherless|teacherlike|teacherness|teachership|teachery|teleteacher|underteacher|unteacher\n|schoolteacher\n|substitute teacher\n|supply teacher\n|teacher's pet|teacher bird|team teacher\n|teacherly\n|teacheress<ll:archaic>\n|parent-teacher-student association|plant teacher|school teacher|student teacher|teacher work day|teacher workday|teacher-centered}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{see translation subpage|Noun}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aceehrt|cheater|hectare|rechate|recheat|reteach}}\n\n{{cln|en|agent nouns}}\n{{C|en|Education|Fingers|Occupations|People}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|es|tícher}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|teacher}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|tícher|hyph=tea.cher}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|mfbysense|#s}}\n\n# {{lb|es|colloquial|student's}} a {{l|en|teacher}}, most commonly an [[ESL]] {{l|en|teacher}}\n#: {{syn|es|profe|profesor}}\n#: {{rfquote-sense|es}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* {{es-unadapted}}\n\n{{C|es|Education|Occupations}}"}}